**/bin
**/obj

# node_modules — must be exhaustive on Windows. BuildKit's context
# walker tries to stat workspace symlinks (pnpm uses NTFS junctions
# for `@aelvory/*` and many vendor pkgs) before applying ignores; if
# one fails, the build aborts with "file cannot be accessed by the
# system". Listing the well-known locations explicitly stops the
# walker from descending in the first place.
node_modules
**/node_modules
**/node_modules/**
apps/desktop/node_modules
apps/desktop/node_modules/**
apps/web/node_modules
apps/web/node_modules/**
apps/server.tests/bin
apps/server.tests/obj
packages/core/node_modules
packages/core/node_modules/**
packages/i18n/node_modules
packages/i18n/node_modules/**
packages/crypto/node_modules
packages/crypto/node_modules/**
packages/scripting/node_modules
packages/scripting/node_modules/**

**/dist
**/target
**/.vs
**/.vscode
**/.idea
**/.git
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example
**/openapi.json
packages/core/src/generated

